  "body": "### Description\r\n\r\n*Type*: Bug\r\n\r\n*Summary*: In the group chat: if user types non-existing recipient name then for send transaction app uses the previous username used before. It's expected that error message will be shown \"Wrong address. Recipient address must be specified\"\r\n\r\n#### Expected behavior\r\nerror message will be shown \"Wrong address. Recipient address must be specified\"\r\n#### Actual behavior\r\nvalid username from previous send transaction is used\r\n\r\n### Reproduction\r\nvideo: https://drive.google.com/open?id=0Bz3t9zSg1wb7OGdobjM4dnJBMWs\r\n- Open Status\r\n- Open group chat\r\n- send to some existing contact 0.1 eth. Do not confirm transaction and return to the group chat (tap on x in the top left corner)\r\n- tap on /send command, do not select username from suggestions. Type some non-existing name in the input field \"blabla\" and 0.2 as amount\r\n- tap on send button. \r\n\r\n* Status version: 0.9.8-59-gda60a65b+\r\n* Operating System: \r\nReal device Samsung Galaxy S7, Android 7.0\r\nReal device iPhone 7 plus, iOS 10.3.2\r\n",
